President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the state of South Dakota and authorized federal assistance to support recovery efforts from a severe storm, straight-line winds, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred between June 11 and June 14, 2022. The federal funding will be provided to state, tribal, and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, funding will be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Alana B. Kuhn has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.